# C# Conventions

## Framework & Language

- Target `net8.0` (LTS). Nullable reference types enabled. Implicit usings enabled.
- Use file-scoped namespaces.
- Prefer `async Task` / `async Task<T>` for all I/O operations (serial, file, network).

## CLI

- Use `System.CommandLine` for argument parsing in BeaconCtl.Cli.
- Root command: `beaconctl`. Subcommands are not used — options go directly on the root command.

## Logging

- Use `Microsoft.Extensions.Logging.ILogger<T>` throughout.
- Log timestamps, COM port, bytes sent/received, and errors.
- Console logging for CLI; file logging when `--log-file` is specified.

## Exit Codes

| Code | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| 0 | Success |
| 1 | General / unknown error |
| 2 | COM port error (missing, access denied, timeout) |
| 3 | Protocol mismatch / relay did not respond |

## Serial

- Use `System.IO.Ports.SerialPort` — no third-party serial libraries.
- Always dispose serial ports in `finally` or via `using`.
- Default: 9600 baud, 8 data bits, no parity, 1 stop bit.

## Project References

- BeaconCtl.Cli depends on BeaconCtl.Core.
- BeaconCtl.StatusEngine depends on BeaconCtl.Core.
- BeaconCtl.Core has no project references (leaf dependency).
